    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Hello there! I can certainly help you draft that rejection email, but I must warn you that the thought of a senior developer leaving feels like a sudden shift in the room's temperature, like a goblin sneaking into a well-lit library and dimming the lights just enough to make everyone squint.\n\nHere is a draft that is professional, polite, and hopefully won't cause the candidate to feel like they've been rejected by a goblin horde rather than a hiring committee.\n\n***\n\n**Subject:** Update Regarding Your Application for Senior Developer Position\n\nDear [Candidate Name],\n\nThank you for taking the time to interview for the Senior Developer role at [Company Name]. We were truly impressed by your technical skills and the depth of your experience during our discussions.\n\nHowever, after careful consideration, we have decided to move forward with another candidate whose background aligns slightly more closely with our immediate project needs at this specific moment. We appreciate the time you spent with us and the valuable insights you shared.\n\nWe wish you the very best in your job search and hope our paths cross again in the future.\n\nWarm regards,\n\n[Your Name]\n[Your Title]\n[Company Name]\n\n***\n\n*Note:",
